<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<subsection xml:id="aa-section-earth-subsection-all" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Putting everything together for Earth</title>

    <p>
        As shown in <xref ref="aa-earth-omega" text="type-global" /> below,
    </p>

    <p>
        <md number="yes">
            \vec{\Omega} = \Omega \cos{\phi} \, \hat{j} + \Omega \sin{\phi} \, \hat{k}
        </md>
    </p>

    <p>
        Thus,
        we can find <m>\vec{\Omega} \times \hat{i}</m>,
        <m>\vec{\Omega} \times \hat{j}</m>,
        and <m>\vec{\Omega} \times \hat{k}</m>
        and verify they match the results of
        <xref ref="eqn-total-derivative-i-final-earth" text="type-global" />,
        <xref ref="eqn-total-derivative-j-final-earth" text="type-global" />,
        and <xref ref="eqn-total-derivative-k-final-earth" text="type-global" />,
        respectively.
    </p>

  <p>
    <md number="yes">
        \vec{\Omega} \times \hat{i}
        =
        \Omega \sin{\phi} \, \hat{j}
        - \Omega \cos{\phi} \, \hat{k}
        =
        \frac{D \hat{i}}{Dt}
    </md>
  </p>

  <p>
    <md number="yes">
        \vec{\Omega} \times \hat{j}
        =
        -\Omega \sin{\phi} \, \hat{i}
        =
        \frac{D \hat{j}}{Dt}
    </md>
  </p>

  <p>
    <md number="yes">
        \vec{\Omega} \times \hat{k}
        =
        \Omega \cos{\phi} \, \hat{i}
        =
        \frac{D \hat{k}}{Dt}
    </md>
  </p>

  <p>
    Therefore, the derivation is complete.
  </p>

    <figure xml:id="aa-earth-omega">
        <caption>
            Reproduction of <xref ref="aa-earth-setup" text="type-global" />,
            with a copy of <m>\vec{\Omega}</m> moved to the point of interest on Earth's surface.
        </caption>
        <image source="images/aa-earth-omega.png" width="60%">
            <shortdescription>
                A point on Earth's surface with the local Cartesian coordinate system and the Earth's angular velocity vector placed at that point.
            </shortdescription>
        </image>
    </figure>

</subsection>